    {
      "id": "5axUO8PWshW1uZcU6xeYl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 619.0884548213996,
      "y": 786.2888393805049,
      "width": 539.4595947265625,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aa",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1611102113,
      "version": 541,
      "versionNonce": 359502785,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782181168839,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Difference between Cassandra and Postgres\nCassandra:\n1.  write to a log\n2. write is just an append\n3. memtable (memory writes and flush after an interval)\n4. ack the write\n5. Flush to disk periodically\n\nPostgres: (Read Optimized)\n1. Write log WAL (disk)\n2. Do the DB Write (disk)\n3. Seeking to right spot and changing or adding row",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Difference between Cassandra and Postgres\nCassandra:\n1.  write to a log\n2. write is just an append\n3. memtable (memory writes and flush after an interval)\n4. ack the write\n5. Flush to disk periodically\n\nPostgres: (Read Optimized)\n1. Write log WAL (disk)\n2. Do the DB Write (disk)\n3. Seeking to right spot and changing or adding row",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
